---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
	description:
		"Astro Typefolio is a concise publishing template for researchers and developers.",
	title: "About",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<h1 class="title mb-4">About Astro Typefolio</h1>
	<div class="index-content">
		<p>
			Astro Typefolio is built for researchers and developers who want a
			professional personal site without a heavy product shell. The goal is
			simple: publish writing, notes, project pages, tags, and news updates with
			a presentation that stays elegant, static-fast, and easy to maintain.
		</p>
		<p>
			The template follows Occam&apos;s razor by keeping only the publishing
			surfaces that help readers understand your work quickly. The homepage
			stays concise; this page explains the template&apos;s positioning and
			repository starting point in more detail.
		</p>
		<p>
			If you only need the quick orientation, start on the homepage. If you want
			the fuller capability breakdown before adopting the template, this page is
			the reference surface.
		</p>
		<p>Typefolio ships with the following built-in capabilities:</p>
		<ul class="list-inside list-disc" role="list">
			<li>
				Astro content collections for posts, notes, and tag-driven archive pages
			</li>
			<li>
				Typography-first page layouts with responsive reading rhythm and
				dark/light themes
			</li>
			<li>
				Pinned Posts on the homepage for featured essays, releases, or research
				updates
			</li>
			<li>
				Notes, backlinks, and richer Markdown components for connected long-form
				publishing
			</li>
			<li>
				Giscus comments for discussion on writing that should stay open to
				community feedback
			</li>
			<li>
				Pagefind static search for fast client-side discovery across the built
				site
			</li>
			<li>
				Generated OG image support for articles and social sharing previews
			</li>
			<li>
				Local bilingual fonts for English and Chinese publishing workflows
			</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			Clone or fork the <a
				class="typefolio-link inline-block"
				href="https://github.com/whliao5am/astro-theme-typefolio"
				rel="noreferrer"
				target="_blank">https://github.com/whliao5am/astro-theme-typefolio</a
			> to start from the current template baseline, then tailor the content model,
			visual tone, and navigation to your own work.
		</p>
	</div>
</PageLayout>
